## New DevSpace Setup
When starting a fresh DevSpace with this project:

```bash
# 1. Credentials already in ~/shared/.aws/ (persists across DevSpaces)
# 2. Env file already in ~/shared/myapp-envs/<env>.sh

# 3. Switch to environment (clones repo, installs deps, starts orchestrator)
./scripts/env-switch.sh <env-name>

# 4. If first time on this account:
ENV_FILE=~/shared/myapp-envs/<env>.sh ./scripts/setup-new-account.sh
```

### Persisted in ~/shared/ (survives DevSpace restarts)
- `~/shared/.aws/config` — AWS CLI config (profile names + regions)
- `~/shared/.aws/credentials` — AWS access keys
- `~/shared/myapp-envs/*.sh` — per-environment configs
- `~/shared/myapp-context.md` — this file

