## Architecture Summary
Platform starter with:
- Frontend: React 18 + Vite + TypeScript
- Backend: Node.js Lambda (CommonJS), single bundle packaging
- Infrastructure: CDK v2 TypeScript (fully parameterized, zero hardcoded values)
- AI: Bedrock Claude Haiku (complexity classification)
- Auth: Cognito + RBAC (user, technical, product_manager, admin)
- DB: DynamoDB (users, feature-requests)
- CI/CD: CDK Pipeline (self-mutating)

## RBAC Roles
| Role | Permissions |
|------|-------------|
| user | Submit requests, vote, basic access |
| technical | Accept/override AI complexity |
| product_manager | Approve/reject requests |
| admin | Manage roles, full access |

## Automation Loop
- `./scripts/feature.sh start` — starts orchestrator daemon
- Orchestrator polls DynamoDB for approved requests
- Invokes kiro-cli to implement features automatically
- Deploys via: frontend → S3 sync, backend → Lambda update, infra → CDK Pipeline
- Multi-DevSpace: parallel processing via DynamoDB atomic claims

## How to Resume Work
```bash
# Check if orchestrator is alive
cd /workspace/active && ./scripts/feature.sh status

# If dead (DevSpace hibernated), restart:
ENV_FILE=~/shared/myapp-envs/<env>.sh ./scripts/feature.sh start

# Check recent activity
git log --oneline -5

# Switch environments
./scripts/env-switch.sh --list
./scripts/env-switch.sh <env-name>
```

